ages! What brings you here?

243
00:16:30,512 --> 00:16:32,552
I'm meeting someone.

244
00:16:32,652 --> 00:16:34,298
Working on a story?
You should've hit me up

245
00:16:34,322 --> 00:16:35,682
when you were in the neighborhood.

246
00:16:35,722 --> 00:16:38,038
Your breakup with Hyun
Jin is no reason to cut us off.

247
00:16:38,062 --> 00:16:39,162
You're so cold.

248
00:16:39,692 --> 00:16:40,892
I've just been busy.

249
00:16:41,262 --> 00:16:43,462
You made a big splash
again today. Are you okay?

250
00:16:43,562 --> 00:16:46,802
Why wouldn't I be? The
networks are happy with ratings,

251
00:16:46,862 --> 00:16:51,042
the public has a new target, and
I love having a bigger audience.

252
00:16:51,172 --> 00:16:52,372
It's a win-win.

253
00:16:54,672 --> 00:16:56,472
Hyun Jin's doing well, by the way.

254
00:16:58,682 --> 00:17:00,512
Just in case you were wondering.

255
00:17:02,482 --> 00:17:04,982
Glad to hear it. We should
grab a bite sometime.

256
00:17:05,652 --> 00:17:06,982
I'd love to see CEO Kang too.

257
00:17:13,192 --> 00:17:14,392
(Jo Yoo Jeong)

258
00:17:18,932 --> 00:17:20,132
Hang on a second.

259
00:17:22,972 --> 00:17:24,172
5887?

260
00:17:28,512 --> 00:17:30,072
(Jo Yoo Jeong)

261
00:17:40,152 --> 00:17:42,252
I've got to run. I'll be in touch.

262
00:17:42,692 --> 00:17:43,952
What's the story?

263
00:17:44,292 --> 00:17:46,852
Jun Hyeok, you're on Jo Yoo
Jeong, aren't you? She's our client.

264
00:17:48,132 --> 00:17:49,332
Talk to you later.

265
00:17:57,602 --> 00:17:59,348
(Kang Eun Seok is innocent!
(Punish the lying accuser!)

266
00:17:59,372 --> 00:18:01,002
(Kang Eun Seok is the real victim!)

267
00:18:07,412 --> 00:18:09,282
(Scales of justice are tilted.)

268
00:18:10,682 --> 00:18:11,952
Attorney Yoon. You're back.

269
00:18:12,522 --> 00:18:13,962
Are these from Kang Eun Seok's fans?

270
00:18:14,692 --> 00:18:17,822
- Yes.
- Leave them. They brighten it up.

271
00:18:17,922 --> 00:18:19,602
(Until Kang Eun Seok's name is cleared...)

272
00:18:21,762 --> 00:18:24,192
We never leaked that picture
of Kang Eun Seok's hair loss,

273
00:18:24,292 --> 00:18:26,502
and of course we weren't
the ones who posted it...

274
00:18:26,562 --> 00:18:28,642
- Keep up the good work, everyone.
- That wasn't us.

275
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:30,132
Yes, this is the LnJ Law Firm.

276
00:18:30,332 --> 00:18:31,678
If you keep acting like this,

277
00:18:31,702 --> 00:18:33,418
- Yes.
- We'll have to take legal actions.

278
00:18:33,442 --> 00:18:34,612
I understand that,

279
00:18:35,112 --> 00:18:37,842
but you can't just be so unreasonable...

280
00:18:49,952 --> 00:18:51,162
You're back?

281
00:18:51,762 --> 00:18:52,962
Yes.

282
00:18:57,362 --> 00:19:00,002
- How was court?
- A nightmare.

283
00:19:00,462 --> 00:19:02,222
Let's talk about it when
Shin Jae gets here.

284
00:19:02,372 --> 00:19:03,572
(Jo Yoo Jeong)

285
00:19:05,502 --> 00:19:08,112
We've got another ton of
comments to save as PDFs today.

286
00:19:09,042 --> 00:19:11,442
- For Yoo Jeong?
- No, for you.

287
00:19:11,712 --> 00:19:13,482
You've got Kang Eun Seok beat.

288
00:19:14,682 --> 00:19:16,602
Seriously, the comments
about you are way worse.

289
00:19:16,982 --> 00:19:18,182
Makes me so proud.

290
00:19:19,182 --> 00:19:21,128
Nothing about Yoo Jeong's
identity has been leaked online, right?

291
00:19:21,152 --> 00:19:22,352
I'm keeping an eye on it.

292
00:19:27,362 --> 00:19:31,032
- How was the committee meeting?
- Same old, same old.

293
00:19:39,702 --> 00:19:41,872
My blood sugar is crashing.

294
00:19:42,342 --> 00:19:44,612
- Let's get some food.
- What should we get?

295
00:19:45,382 --> 00:19:46,582
Something delicious.

296
00:19:50,312 --> 00:19:53,852
- Can this food get any better?
- Never.

297
00:19:54,952 --> 00:19:58,122
This tastes like what we
used to eat after school as kids.

298
00:20:00,492 --> 00:20:02,612
This is the only thing I
crave when I'm stressed out.

299
00:20:02,892 --> 00:20:06,232
But why would Jo Yoo Jeong lie?

300
00:20:07,102 --> 00:20:10,872
If not at a club, where? A
dating app? Social media?

301
00:20:10,932 --> 00:20:12,142
No, that's not it.

302
00:20:12,242 --> 00:20:13,518
They even ran forensics on his phone.

303
00:20:13,542 --> 00:20:15,572
The prosecution said it was clean.

304
00:20:15,712 --> 00:20:17,772
And Yoo Jeong refuses to say a single word.

305
00:20:18,082 --> 00:20:20,082
If we can't figure out where they met,

306
00:20:20,182 --> 00:20:21,982
Kang Eun Seok is just going to walk free.

307
00:20:23,012 --> 00:20:24,258
I thought you said you hated spicy food.

308
00:20:24,282 --> 00:20:25,602
And I thought you were on a diet.

309
00:20:26,022 --> 00:20:28,852
Don't you know I've
been all talk for 20 years?

310
00:20:28,922 --> 00:20:31,862
Exactly. That makes me
a good friend for 20 years.

311
00:20:31,962 --> 00:20:34,862
Hey, thanks to you, I
haven't dieted since college.

312
00:20:34,962 --> 00:20:36,992
Here, eat up.

313
00:20:37,062 --> 00:20:39,178
Anyway, if we lose the first trial,

314
00:20:39,202 --> 00:20:41,502
Kang Eun Seok will likely counter sue.

315
00:20:41,672 --> 00:20:45,542
She won't talk, even
facing perjury, false charges.

316
00:20:46,542 --> 00:20:47,742
What is going on?

317
00:20:49,942 --> 00:20:52,742
I think Jun Hyeok has been
in contact with Yoo Jeong.

318
00:20:54,042 --> 00:20:57,112
- Did you see Reporter Lee?
- Yes, I saw him on my way in.

319
00:20:59,022 --> 00:21:00,422
He seemed to be doing well.

320
00:21:03,992 --> 00:21:06,522
I'm sure he is.

321
00:21:08,592 --> 00:21:10,308
Wait, what do you mean?

322
00:21:10,332 --> 00:21:12,362
Jun Hyeok's in contact with Yoo Jeong?

323
00:21:12,962 --> 00:21:16,272
I saw him get a call from her.
I think that's why he was here.

324
00:21:17,572 --> 00:21:21,142
Why don't you go talk to
him? He might know something.

325
00:21:22,642 --> 00:21:24,172
What's the big deal? It's for work.

326
00:21:27,542 --> 00:21:31,322
Yes. We broke up ages
ago. I'll go talk to him.

327
00:21:32,322 --> 00:21:34,522
You deleted his number,
didn't you? Want me to send it?

328
00:21:34,922 --> 00:21:36,122
Yes.

329
00:21:42,292 --> 00:21:44,062
(Lee Jun Hyeok)

330
00:21:53,372 --> 00:21:56,572
What do I do? The trial
was a complete disaster.

331
00:21:57,412 --> 00:22:00,442
Maybe it's better to
tell the truth, even now...

332
00:22:00,742 --> 00:22:02,652
But you know what will happen.

333
00:22:03,452 --> 00:22:04,852
If I tell the truth,

334
00:22:05,752 --> 00:22:08,422
they'll come after me.

335
00:22:09,522 --> 00:22:10,952
I'm terrified.

336
00:22:12,422 --> 00:22:14,192
What am I supposed to do now, Reporter Lee?

337
00:22:33,942 --> 00:22:35,382
(Hyun Jin)

338
00:22:41,822 --> 00:22:44,692
If it's too late, I can
come back another time.

339
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:46,522
Come on in.

340
00:23:01,172 --> 00:23:02,372
You look good.

341
00:23:04,942 --> 00:23:06,682
I am. I'm happy.

342
00:23:20,522 --> 00:23:21,732
Help me.

343
00:23:22,592 --> 00:23:24,192
That's what I came here to say.

344
00:23:25,132 --> 00:23:27,302
You've been talking to Jo
Yoo Jeong, haven't you?

345
00:23:30,872 --> 00:23:33,642
I can't figure out where Yoo
Jeong met Kang Eun Seok.

346
00:23:34,302 --> 00:23:36,672
She's terrified of something
and refuses to talk.

347
00:23:37,342 --> 00:23:40,212
At this rate, the charges against
Kang Eun Seok won't stick.

348
00:23:42,582 --> 00:23:44,482
You know something, don't you?

349
00:23:48,092 --> 00:23:49,292
Everything you know

350
00:23:50,222 --> 00:23:51,722
is everything I know.

351
00:23:57,892 --> 00:24:00,732
Jun Hyeok. We were
together for seven years.

352
00:24:01,362 --> 00:24:05,042
We were together for way too
long not to know when you're lying.

353
00:24:08,242 --> 00:24:10,572
Help me out. Please.

354
00:24:16,982 --> 00:24:18,182
More tea?

355
00:24:21,622 --> 00:24:22,822
I'm telling the truth.

356
00:24:23,152 --> 00:24:27,092
I met Jo Yoo Jeong through
the Kang Eun Seok case. That's it.

357
00:24:29,492 --> 00:24:32,202
So there is something else.

358
00:24:33,002 --> 00:24:36,172
Something much bigger behind Jo Yoo Jeong.

359
00:24:39,902 --> 00:24:43,942
I got you this in France, remember?
Nike, the goddess of victory.

360
00:24:44,782 --> 00:24:45,942
- That's...
- You said

361
00:24:46,012 --> 00:24:49,812
it brought you good luck.
You'd put it here for a big scoop.

362
00:24:50,482 --> 00:24:52,682
Like the presidential
candidate's slush fund scandal.

363
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:55,262
And when you broke the story
on that secret political advisor.

364
00:24:55,852 --> 00:24:58,522
What is it? What exactly
are you digging into?

365
00:25:01,532 --> 00:25:02,762
You should leave.

366
00:25:03,862 --> 00:25:05,262
Look me in the eye and tell me.

367
00:25:06,232 --> 00:25:07,432
What is it?

368
00:25:15,512 --> 00:25:16,772
A sex trade scandal.

369
00:25:19,512 --> 00:25:20,712
Sex trade?

370
00:25:22,652 --> 00:25:26,752
You mean Yoo Jeong met Kang
Eun Seok through prostitution?

371
00:25:30,922 --> 00:25:33,562
So it's not just a simple case
of prostitution. How big is this?

372
00:25:34,462 --> 00:25:35,692
If this gets out,

373
00:25:37,062 --> 00:25:38,742
it'll turn the entire country upside down.

374
00:25:39,402 --> 00:25:41,632
- What?
- I can't tell you more. Not yet.

375
00:25:42,302 --> 00:25:43,348
It'll put you in danger too.

376
00:25:43,372 --> 00:25:45,942
I promise you'll be the first
to know when the time comes.

377
00:25:46,602 --> 00:25:47,802
But not now.

378
00:26:04,392 --> 00:26:05,592
You're unbelievable.

379
00:26:06,962 --> 00:26:08,892
Why do you still have this?

380
00:26:13,132 --> 00:26:14,332
Are you crazy?

381
00:26:15,072 --> 00:26:17,832
I've regretted it ever
since. The way we broke up.

382
00:26:19,202 --> 00:26:20,972
I never should have come here.

383
00:26:22,772 --> 00:26:24,942
This is wrong. We shouldn't
see each other again.

384
00:26:27,112 --> 00:26:28,852
What more is there to say?

385
00:26:32,552 --> 00:26:33,752
I missed you.

386
00:26:59,212 --> 00:27:00,482
I must be crazy.

387
00:27:01,282 --> 00:27:02,612
I'm crazy.

388
00:27:03,582 --> 00:27:07,182
Seriously, Hyun Jin. You're losing it.

389
00:27:07,652 --> 00:27:09,052
(Shin Jae)

390
00:27:20,332 --> 00:27:22,932
- Hey.
- Did you meet with Reporter Lee?

391
00:27:27,042 --> 00:27:28,512
A prostitution scandal?

392
00:27:28,912 --> 00:27:31,392
So that must be why Yoo Jeong
wouldn't tell us where they met.

393
00:27:31,612 --> 00:27:33,692
She was afraid the
prostitution part would come out.

394
00:27:34,812 --> 00:27:36,482
This is going to hurt our case.

395
00:27:37,052 --> 00:27:38,282
So what do we do now?

396
00:27:38,682 --> 00:27:42,722
Nothing's changed. Jo Yoo Jeong
was clear that she never consented.

397
00:27:42,892 --> 00:27:46,492
Does meeting through prostitution
mean it's okay to rape someone?

398
00:27:46,862 --> 00:27:50,462
Anyway, it seems like the scandal is huge.

399
00:27:50,632 --> 00:27:52,832
Even Jun Hyeok seemed overwhelmed by it.

400
00:27:53,662 --> 00:27:55,732
So you just backed off and left?

401
00:27:57,472 --> 00:27:58,972
Are you kidding? Of course not.

402
00:28:00,042 --> 00:28:01,242
(Cheongdam New Pair SH 5pm)

403
00:28:03,742 --> 00:28:07,142
I think he has another
source besides Yoo Jeong.

404
00:28:07,182 --> 00:28:10,482
If Yoo Jeong won't talk, we
should try to approach them.

405
00:28:13,952 --> 00:28:15,152
By the way,

406
00:28:16,692 --> 00:28:18,362
nothing else happened, right?

407
00:28:19,592 --> 00:28:20,962
What do you mean?

408
00:28:22,592 --> 00:28:24,932
Never mind. Just asking.

409
00:28:25,532 --> 00:28:28,232
- Good work. Get some rest.
- Hey, wait!

410
00:28:43,982 --> 00:28:46,182
- Why are you so late?
- What?

411
00:28:50,522 --> 00:28:53,122
Don't you have the night shift today?

412
00:28:53,492 --> 00:28:56,132
I just stopped by. You
know what tonight is.

413
00:28:56,992 --> 00:28:58,932
Hang on. I'll wash up and be right out.

414
00:29:09,512 --> 00:29:11,212
- Hey, Hyun Jin!
- Yes?

415
00:29:11,372 --> 00:29:14,082
I left out your folic acid
too. Go ahead and take it.

416
00:29:46,642 --> 00:29:51,012
- Stay strong, Kang Eun Seok!
- Stay strong, Kang Eun Seok!

417
00:29:51,082 --> 00:29:52,558
(We love you, Kang Eun Seok.
(Stay strong, Kang Eun Seok.)

418
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:55,252
Mr. Kang, what verdict are you expecting?

419
00:29:55,322 --> 00:29:57,022
How are you feeling ahead of the verdict?

420
00:29:58,192 --> 00:30:01,762
I have faith that the truth will prevail.

421
00:30:02,932 --> 00:30:05,278
Depending on the verdict, what
are your plans for the future?

422
00:30:05,302 --> 00:30:06,942
Do you have any last words for the court?

423
00:30:11,332 --> 00:30:13,772
Case number 2025 Gohap 308.

424
00:30:14,172 --> 00:30:17,472
For the defendant, Kang Eun
Seok, we will now deliver the verdict.

425
00:30:20,742 --> 00:30:22,412
- Here he comes!
- Here he comes!

426
00:30:22,482 --> 00:30:23,758
- Here he comes!
- Here he comes!

427
00:30:23,782 --> 00:30:25,982
Mr. Kang Eun Seok was
acquitted in the first trial.

428
00:30:26,022 --> 00:30:28,142
As the victim's attorney,
do you accept this verdict?

429
00:30:28,222 --> 00:30:31,452
We hear his side plans a counter
suit for false accusation and defamation.

430
00:30:31,522 --> 00:30:33,198
Will you continue to represent the victim?

431
00:30:33,222 --> 00:30:34,798
The "High School Honey
Trap" is a big trend these days.

432
00:30:34,822 --> 00:30:35,808
Have you heard of it?

433
00:30:35,832 --> 00:30:39,462
Yes, I've heard of it.
In an article you wrote.

434
00:30:40,302 --> 00:30:43,372
But I'm sure you've also heard
of "Trash Reporter," haven't you?

435
00:30:43,702 --> 00:30:45,182
I'm guessing you hear that one a lot.

436
00:30:47,642 --> 00:30:50,142
This isn't the Supreme Court.
This was only the first trial.

437
00:30:50,372 --> 00:30:52,982
We'll see who's lying when
we take this all the way.

438
00:30:55,042 --> 00:30:59,482
And when the truth comes
out, there will be a price to pay.

439
00:31:02,952 --> 00:31:03,998
(Kang acquitted, Lack of evidence)

440
00:31:04,022 --> 00:31:05,168
(Kang, "I'll return with good work")

441
00:31:05,192 --> 00:31:06,738
(Despite acquittal, public
outrage remains high)

442
00:31:06,762 --> 00:31:08,442
(Kang Eun Seok's Trial Ends, "Not Guilty")

443
00:31:08,792 --> 00:31:09,808
(Her claims nearly ruined him.)

444
00:31:09,832 --> 00:31:11,072
(He's rich, so he's not guilty)

445
00:31:11,332 --> 00:31:13,438
(Trial Over: A Pyrrhic Victory? Law
versus Public, A Renewed Debate)

446
00:31:13,462 --> 00:31:15,022
(Concerns Over Secondary Victimization)

447
00:31:15,062 --> 00:31:17,902
(Kang Not Guilty, Questions Remain
Kang's Apology and Silence at Court)

448
00:31:19,302 --> 00:31:22,242
I'm sincerely grateful
for the court's fair ruling.

449
00:31:22,612 --> 00:31:26,642
However, one person's malicious
lie almost cost me everything.

450
00:31:27,482 --> 00:31:30,582
I hope that no one else has
to be victimized so unjustly,

451
00:31:30,882 --> 00:31:34,222
and I will continue to live
proudly, refusing to bow to injustice.

452
00:31:35,192 --> 00:31:38,252
I also want to thank my fans, who
have supported me through this,

453
00:31:38,662 --> 00:31:41,422
and I promise to repay you
with great work in the future.

454
00:31:42,092 --> 00:31:43,308
(Poor Kang Eun Seok.)

455
00:31:43,332 --> 00:31:44,772
(Latching on for money. Get a life.)

456
00:31:45,662 --> 00:31:47,762
(Anyone want to see the
seductress's face and name?)

457
00:31:47,862 --> 00:31:50,062
(Hot Girls Available. Book
Now. 20 Percent Off Special)

458
00:31:54,702 --> 00:31:56,712
(Attorney Yoon Ra Young)

459
00:32:08,952 --> 00:32:11,298
The person you called is unavailable.

460
00:32:11,322 --> 00:32:12,862
Leave a message after the tone.

461
00:32:16,532 --> 00:32:17,732
She's not picking up.

462
00:32:18,462 --> 00:32:20,162
I guess I should go check on her.

463
00:32:20,302 --> 00:32:21,478
Let's leave her be.

464
00:32:21,502 --> 00:32:23,508
It looks like she doesn't
want to see anyone today.

465
00:32:23,532 --> 00:32:24,732
Just leave her be.

466
00:32:24,772 --> 00:32:28,872
Jo Yoo Jeong needs to realize
the consequences of her lies.

467
00:32:30,012 --> 00:32:34,742
But public opinion is terrible.
Will the prosecution really appeal?

468
00:32:34,942 --> 00:32:37,082
If they won't, we'll make them.

469
00:32:37,352 --> 00:32:38,458
The key to the appeal

470
00:32:38,482 --> 00:32:41,182
is proving where Yoo Jeong
and Kang Eun Seok met.

471
00:32:41,282 --> 00:32:44,452
If we can't prove that,
there's no point in appealing.

472
00:32:46,092 --> 00:32:47,992
Any word from Reporter Lee since then?

473
00:32:50,062 --> 00:32:52,932
Then we have no choice. Next plan.

474
00:32:54,332 --> 00:32:56,602
Cheongdam New Pair.

475
00:32:57,632 --> 00:32:58,972
SH.

476
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:00,542
(Cheongdam New Pair SH 5pm)

477
00:33:04,212 --> 00:33:07,042
- What about the signed receipt?
- The director said he lost it.

478
00:33:08,042 --> 00:33:10,012
Normally, we don't have
to bill them from here.

479
00:33:10,252 --> 00:33:13,322
You're expected to get them condoms,
what's the big deal about a bar tab?

480
00:33:13,422 --> 00:33:16,522
Tell me about it. I wish they'd just
pay their darn tab on their way out.

481
00:33:17,222 --> 00:33:18,422
July 12.

482
00:33:20,022 --> 00:33:22,132
SH...

483
00:33:22,192 --> 00:33:24,262
(Seon Hwa)

484
00:33:29,402 --> 00:33:30,602
Are you sure it was July 12?

485
00:33:32,502 --> 00:33:34,942
Oh, my gosh. Oh, no. What am I going to do?

486
00:33:35,712 --> 00:33:40,042
- It must be next door. Sorry.
- Seon Hwa, someone's here for you.

487
00:33:58,532 --> 00:34:00,232
A consolation drink for the losing team.

488
00:34:00,462 --> 00:34:03,532
How gracious. A defeated soldier
receiving a drink from Your Majesty.

489
00:34:09,772 --> 00:34:11,012
You're going to appeal, right?

490
00:34:11,072 --> 00:34:15,482
Come on, you know the deal. First,
Jo Yoo Jeong is not cooperating,

491
00:34:15,582 --> 00:34:17,852
and her testimony is full of holes.

492
00:34:18,482 --> 00:34:19,922
I'll patch them up.

493
00:34:20,852 --> 00:34:23,422
My boss is already giving
me looks to drop the case.

494
00:34:24,422 --> 00:34:25,862
I can smooth things over with him.

495
00:34:28,992 --> 00:34:33,232
Anyway, how long are you going
to keep up this little charity project?

496
00:34:33,362 --> 00:34:37,332
You're the heir to Korea's top
firm, so why play in this dinky office?

497
00:34:37,502 --> 00:34:39,672
Cut it out and go back to your palace.

498
00:34:39,972 --> 00:34:43,272
Then what about you, who's trying
to call dibs on a spot in my palace?

499
00:34:43,412 --> 00:34:45,172
What should I do about
that, Prosecutor Lee?

500
00:34:48,952 --> 00:34:51,782
Anyway, no matter what you do,
an appeal is out of the question.

501
00:34:52,752 --> 00:34:55,432
- Kang Eun Seok is a beloved star.
- Here's the Kang Eun Seok file.

502
00:34:55,652 --> 00:35:00,422
Public opinion is too against us.
You have to bend with the wind.

503
00:35:00,562 --> 00:35:04,268
I don't want to get my neck
chopped off for nothing. Get it?

504
00:35:04,292 --> 00:35:05,832
I'll change that too.

505
00:35:06,632 --> 00:35:07,832
What?

506
00:35:08,532 --> 00:35:11,532
The direction of the wind.
From a headwind into a tailwind.

507
00:35:14,702 --> 00:35:17,312
I'll set the table. All you have to do is eat.

508
00:35:21,082 --> 00:35:23,012
You people are ridiculous.

509
00:35:23,312 --> 00:35:24,588
If you're so curious about
my talk with Reporter Lee,

510
00:35:24,612 --> 00:35:26,482
why don't you ask him yourselves?

511
00:35:26,552 --> 00:35:27,752
Why are you coming after me?

512
00:35:28,722 --> 00:35:30,828
That's it. I'm calling Reporter
Lee to ask him what this is about.

513
00:35:30,852 --> 00:35:33,362
- If you're really his friends.
- That's enough.

514
00:35:34,162 --> 00:35:35,908
Do you ever have to
deal with difficult clients?

515
00:35:35,932 --> 00:35:37,568
What about the owners?
Ever had one refuse to pay?

516
00:35:37,592 --> 00:35:38,802
Think carefully.

517
00:35:39,362 --> 00:35:41,832
It can't hurt to know a lawyer, can it?

518
00:35:46,042 --> 00:35:49,742
Fine, spit it out. Why are you here?

519
00:35:49,772 --> 00:35:51,048
You saw the news, right?

520
00:35:51,072 --> 00:35:54,412
Actor Kang Eun Seok was
acquitted of raping a minor.

521
00:35:54,442 --> 00:35:57,112
We want to know where
Kang Eun Seok met the victim.

522
00:35:57,182 --> 00:36:01,452
That jerk, Kang Eun Seok.
He's still up to his old tricks.

523
00:36:02,052 --> 00:36:03,522
You've met him?

524
00:36:04,152 --> 00:36:07,168
Is there a girl working in
Gangnam who hasn't sat on his lap?

525
00:36:07,192 --> 00:36:08,562
That jerk is a total sicko.

526
00:36:08,692 --> 00:36:11,132
He only goes after
underage girls. That scumbag.

527
00:36:11,392 --> 00:36:13,232
Did it happen to you personally?

528
00:36:13,702 --> 00:36:15,548
If there's any way you
could testify for the appeal...

529
00:36:15,572 --> 00:36:18,532
Lady, I'm on probation, okay?

530
00:36:18,632 --> 00:36:21,842
You want me to admit I sold my
body? Are you out of your mind?

531
00:36:22,412 --> 00:36:24,772
Besides, you'll never be
able to nail Kang Eun Seok.

532
00:36:26,582 --> 00:36:27,782
You see this?

533
00:36:29,782 --> 00:36:32,852
You know how I ended up like
this? It was all Kang Eun Seok.

534
00:36:33,322 --> 00:36:36,722
When I got busted for drugs,
I ratted out everyone I knew.

535
00:36:36,752 --> 00:36:39,322
But only Kang Eun Seok's
name vanished from my statement.

536
00:36:40,422 --> 00:36:41,622
I wonder why.

537
00:36:43,432 --> 00:36:45,462
Who in the world is backing Kang Eun Seok?

538
00:36:46,532 --> 00:36:49,052
You know, don't you, Seon Hwa?
That's why you met Reporter Lee.

539
00:36:51,532 --> 00:36:55,772
That girl, Kang Eun Seok's
victim. Just leave her alone.

540
00:36:55,872 --> 00:36:58,072
She could get seriously
hurt because of you.

541
00:37:02,612 --> 00:37:04,052
I need 1,200 dollars.

542
00:37:04,082 --> 00:37:07,282
My fee for a session. You
made me miss my next client.

543
00:37:21,632 --> 00:37:23,648
You saw the verdict from
the first trial, didn't you?

544
00:37:23,672 --> 00:37:26,702
If Yoo Jeong is wronged like this,
will you really be okay with that?

545
00:40:34,822 --> 00:40:36,062
Hello.

546
00:40:38,862 --> 00:40:40,132
Her personal info was leaked?

547
00:40:51,212 --> 00:40:52,412
Just this, please.

548
00:40:58,582 --> 00:40:59,822
That's 3.2 dollars.

549
00:41:00,882 --> 00:41:02,082
(Jo Yoo Jeong)

550
00:41:04,922 --> 00:41:06,198
(Jo Yoo Jeong, 18. Gyeongseon Girls' High)

551
00:41:06,222 --> 00:41:08,342
(29 Yeonbuk-ro 63-gil,
Seoul. Semi-basement. Get it?)

552
00:41:20,002 --> 00:41:21,978
(Can she even show her
face? Going to her house now.)

553
00:41:22,002 --> 00:41:23,318
(Darn, she's totally my type, though)

554
00:41:23,342 --> 00:41:24,648
(Beware of honey traps.
(Let's teach her a lesson.)

555
00:41:24,672 --> 00:41:25,649
(5 mins away. Coming, Yoo Jeong.)

556
00:41:25,673 --> 00:41:26,818
(Who were her lawyers? Trash them.)

557
00:41:26,842 --> 00:41:28,118
(Best Comment: Hope
property values don't drop.)

558
00:41:28,142 --> 00:41:32,082
(You have a new notification)

559
00:41:36,922 --> 00:41:38,592
Yoo Min, don't come home today.

560
00:41:39,292 --> 00:41:41,822
Whatever you do, don't come home today.

561
00:41:46,002 --> 00:41:47,508
The "High School Honey
Trap" is a big trend these days.

562
00:41:47,532 --> 00:41:48,532
Have you heard of it?

563
00:41:48,732 --> 00:41:50,202
Yes, I've heard of it.

564
00:41:50,872 --> 00:41:53,742
But I'm sure you've also heard
of "Trash Reporter," haven't you?

565
00:41:54,642 --> 00:41:57,042
This isn't the Supreme Court.
This was only the first trial.

566
00:41:57,542 --> 00:41:59,812
We'll see who's lying when
we take this all the way.

567
00:42:01,112 --> 00:42:05,952
And when the truth comes
out, there will be a price to pay.

568
00:42:07,482 --> 00:42:09,202
(Kang Eun Seok Acquitted of Sexual Assault)

569
00:42:56,402 --> 00:42:57,602
Come on in.

570
00:43:02,242 --> 00:43:03,482
Thanks for coming all this way.

571
00:43:04,012 --> 00:43:05,572
Can I get you something to drink first?

572
00:43:07,282 --> 00:43:08,482
No, I'm fine.

573
00:43:16,522 --> 00:43:17,842
Should we get started right away?

574
00:43:18,422 --> 00:43:20,692
One at a time? Or all at once?

575
00:43:48,482 --> 00:43:49,692
Where on earth have you been?

576
00:43:50,452 --> 00:43:51,652
What about your phone?

577
00:43:52,452 --> 00:43:55,222
My battery...

578
00:44:20,682 --> 00:44:22,282
Eat. Even if you don't have an appetite.

579
00:44:24,422 --> 00:44:26,862
I had the posts taken
down. I'll keep monitoring it,

580
00:44:27,322 --> 00:44:30,162
and I'm suing every single
person who's slandering you.

581
00:44:31,562 --> 00:44:32,802
I want to die.

582
00:44:35,002 --> 00:44:36,202
Why should you die?

583
00:44:36,832 --> 00:44:40,242
Kill, don't die. That's the
mindset. To spite them all.

584
00:44:41,272 --> 00:44:44,442
If you're tied up, bite. If
they gag you, headbutt them.

585
00:44:45,042 --> 00:44:47,782
Don't waste time on dying,
figure out how to survive.

586
00:44:48,742 --> 00:44:50,682
That's what I would do.

587
00:45:05,162 --> 00:45:08,202
Did you meet Kang Eun Seok
because he paid you for sex?

588
00:45:10,302 --> 00:45:14,072
I know you know this, but
lying and being so reckless

589
00:45:14,672 --> 00:45:16,012
was a terrible mistake.

590
00:45:19,312 --> 00:45:22,812
But the one who should be ashamed

591
00:45:23,652 --> 00:45:25,492
is Kang Eun Seok, the
man who paid to buy you.

592
00:45:25,912 --> 00:45:30,152
And the ones with more
to answer for than you

593
00:45:30,292 --> 00:45:33,052
are the adults who didn't teach you
how dangerous and wrong that was.

594
00:45:34,862 --> 00:45:38,562
We are going to fight
for you until the very end.

595
00:45:38,732 --> 00:45:39,932
But

596
00:45:40,432 --> 00:45:41,962
you need to start helping us too.

597
00:45:43,002 --> 00:45:44,202
Do you understand what I mean?

598
00:45:49,742 --> 00:45:52,542
Okay, good. All right, then...

599
00:45:57,952 --> 00:45:59,472
First, let's get you something to eat.

600
00:46:19,132 --> 00:46:22,002
So, is Jo Yoo Jeong
at your place right now?

601
00:46:22,702 --> 00:46:24,812
Yes. I waited until she
was asleep before I left.

602
00:46:25,312 --> 00:46:28,282
When I'm done here, I'll ask
where she met Kang Eun Seok.

603
00:46:28,742 --> 00:46:31,782
- Is she okay?
- How could she be? She's only 18.

604
00:46:33,452 --> 00:46:34,952
The trial was closed to the public,

605
00:46:35,352 --> 00:46:37,912
and she never came to our
office to avoid exposing her identity.

606
00:46:38,552 --> 00:46:41,362
So what kind of jerk leaked her identity?

607
00:46:48,232 --> 00:46:49,432
Swhat?

608
00:46:50,932 --> 00:46:53,402
Kang Eun Seok arrested on drug charges?

609
00:46:53,642 --> 00:46:56,672
Our tenth anniversary
present. Do you like it?

610
00:46:58,412 --> 00:47:01,312
But I heard Lee Seon Hwa
clammed up when the cops arrived.

611
00:47:01,412 --> 00:47:02,612
Yes, it seemed that way.

612
00:47:03,112 --> 00:47:04,852
Some big shot must have gotten to her.

613
00:47:05,412 --> 00:47:06,752
So?

614
00:47:07,022 --> 00:47:08,542
So, I went to see the Chief of Police.

615
00:47:10,452 --> 00:47:12,332
You definitely knocked
him down a weight class.

616
00:47:12,492 --> 00:47:15,762
For the appeal, we fight a
junkie, not the beloved son-in-law.

617
00:47:17,532 --> 00:47:20,832
You head to the hotel. I'm
going to the police station.

618
00:47:20,862 --> 00:47:22,232
The police station? What for?

619
00:47:22,402 --> 00:47:25,932
I don't know. Maybe I should
get Kang Eun Seok's autograph?

620
00:47:26,342 --> 00:47:28,262
I won't be able to once
he's behind bars, right?

621
00:47:32,442 --> 00:47:34,242
You know, sometimes I think.

622
00:47:34,812 --> 00:47:39,652
I'm so darn glad she's our
friend and not our enemy.

623
00:47:39,982 --> 00:47:41,622
I bet Shin Jae thought the same thing.

624
00:47:42,052 --> 00:47:44,752
About you, when you turned
the tables on my stalker.

625
00:47:50,562 --> 00:47:51,762
Hang on.

626
00:47:53,632 --> 00:47:54,902
Hey, it's me.

627
00:47:55,862 --> 00:47:57,102
Are you free tonight?

628
00:47:57,972 --> 00:47:59,372
Look, about the other night...

629
00:48:00,242 --> 00:48:02,072
It was a mistake. A one-time thing.

630
00:48:02,572 --> 00:48:05,072
I'll give you the files.
I've changed my mind.

631
00:48:05,912 --> 00:48:07,242
Be at my place by 8pm.

632
00:48:12,982 --> 00:48:14,282
You look better on screen.

633
00:48:15,652 --> 00:48:17,532
What a shame. I was
so looking forward to this.

634
00:48:18,292 --> 00:48:20,332
You, on the other hand,
are just my type, Attorney.

635
00:48:20,522 --> 00:48:22,082
You should've shown up in court sooner.

636
00:48:22,222 --> 00:48:24,108
It would've given me
something to look forward to.

637
00:48:24,132 --> 00:48:26,732
Sorry. I'm not into long-distance.

638
00:48:27,502 --> 00:48:29,342
Prison is just a little
too far from my place.

639
00:48:35,002 --> 00:48:37,682
The evidence I turned over to the
Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency.

640
00:48:38,542 --> 00:48:41,518
Security footage of you at an ATM in
a Seocho-dong convenience store

641
00:48:41,542 --> 00:48:42,812
depositing drug cash.

642
00:48:43,382 --> 00:48:45,882
Video of you at the fire hydrant
across from the Maegun Hotel,

643
00:48:46,012 --> 00:48:48,622
picking up five bags of
meth from a dead drop.

644
00:48:49,122 --> 00:48:52,022
Two grams of meth and some
weed were found at your place earlier.

645
00:48:52,452 --> 00:48:56,532
And I'm sure you know what
your hair follicle test will show.

646
00:48:58,792 --> 00:49:00,032
And?

647
00:49:01,102 --> 00:49:04,532
But there's one more thing I
haven't turned over to the police.

648
00:49:07,972 --> 00:49:10,292
Turns out you were a dealer
in the entertainment industry.

649
00:49:10,572 --> 00:49:12,712
You were quite generous with it too.

650
00:49:15,182 --> 00:49:19,182
You know the sentencing difference
between use and distribution.

651
00:49:22,222 --> 00:49:24,592
So, what do you want in exchange?

652
00:49:31,392 --> 00:49:32,662
Who's backing you?

653
00:49:37,072 --> 00:49:38,352
Where did you meet Jo Yoo Jeong?

654
00:49:46,742 --> 00:49:48,412
Come on. You're obviously bluffing.

655
00:49:48,782 --> 00:49:50,612
I'm holding a straight flush.

656
00:49:50,952 --> 00:49:53,272
Who in their right mind folds
that to take a garbage hand?

657
00:49:56,022 --> 00:49:57,222
Is that so?

658
00:49:58,792 --> 00:50:02,892
If people find out where you met
Jo Yoo Jeong, your game falls apart.

659
00:50:05,462 --> 00:50:07,622
What are you saying? You're
barking up the wrong tree.

660
00:50:08,302 --> 00:50:09,662
Thanks for confirming that for me.

661
00:50:10,232 --> 00:50:12,272
I wanted to hear it from
you myself, Kang Eun Seok.

662
00:50:13,372 --> 00:50:16,512
So it wasn't just a rumor. A
sex scandal to rock the nation.

663
00:50:16,572 --> 00:50:18,972
Are you really going
to leak that? Right now?

664
00:50:19,712 --> 00:50:21,412
Actually, I already leaked it.

665
00:50:22,482 --> 00:50:24,762
I see things through to the
end, even with a losing hand.

666
00:50:25,082 --> 00:50:26,252
And I've never lost.

667
00:50:41,762 --> 00:50:43,272
(LnJ 10th Anniversary Gala)

668
00:50:49,142 --> 00:50:52,172
- Business is going well, I trust?
- Yes, it's going great, thank you.

669
00:50:59,382 --> 00:51:00,652
Welcome.

670
00:51:01,082 --> 00:51:03,292
- Please see our guests are seated.
- Hello.

671
00:51:03,392 --> 00:51:04,622
- Hello.
- It's been a while.

672
00:51:04,722 --> 00:51:07,692
- Good to see you.
- You as well. I'll see you later.

673
00:51:10,862 --> 00:51:12,062
Counselor.

674
00:51:13,932 --> 00:51:15,162
I'll come say hi again later.

675
00:51:15,932 --> 00:51:17,132
Okay.

676
00:51:18,732 --> 00:51:19,942
Hello.

677
00:51:20,202 --> 00:51:22,002
It's been a while.
You've been well, I hope.

678
00:51:27,582 --> 00:51:29,242
Did you hear? Choi Min Hye got a job.

679
00:51:30,082 --> 00:51:32,442
She said she'll stop by when
she comes to Seoul next month.

680
00:51:32,852 --> 00:51:36,182
Guys, we got a letter from
Seon Mi. She passed her GED!

681
00:51:37,392 --> 00:51:40,792
- Gosh, good for her.
- Who sent the wine?

682
00:51:43,992 --> 00:51:45,392
It's a 2005 vintage.

683
00:51:48,502 --> 00:51:49,978
(Congratulations on your 10th anniversary.)

684
00:51:50,002 --> 00:51:53,302
- I bet it's from the alumni.
- Right. It's from the school.

685
00:51:55,502 --> 00:51:56,872
Gosh, seriously...

686
00:51:58,872 --> 00:52:01,112
Ten years just flew by.

687
00:52:03,282 --> 00:52:06,212
But I don't think I could do
this for another ten years.

688
00:52:06,482 --> 00:52:11,392
We have to play by my mom's
rules to survive another ten years.

689
00:52:11,792 --> 00:52:15,662
Should we go to Jeju for
our 20th? Just the 3 of us?

690
00:52:16,022 --> 00:52:18,292
Forget that. We should go to the Maldives.

691
00:52:20,732 --> 00:52:22,692
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

692
00:52:23,172 --> 00:52:25,232
And the opening remarks
go to Yoon Ra Young.

693
00:52:25,532 --> 00:52:28,972
- Seriously?
- I got LASIK. I hate flashes.

694
00:52:29,912 --> 00:52:32,872
I'm heading back to the party.
You two come down in a little bit.

695
00:52:39,752 --> 00:52:40,952
What are you doing?

696
00:52:41,652 --> 00:52:43,492
You're not trying to
sneak out alone, are you?

697
00:52:44,022 --> 00:52:47,062
I'm going to get our present.
Our tenth anniversary present.

698
00:52:48,622 --> 00:52:52,932
- A present?
- Jun Hyeok's promised files.

699
00:52:53,502 --> 00:52:55,832
We can win the appeal.

700
00:52:57,232 --> 00:52:58,432
I'll call you.

701
00:52:58,702 --> 00:53:00,772
- What?
- Hwang Hyun Jin.

702
00:53:00,842 --> 00:53:02,042
What?

703
00:53:03,442 --> 00:53:04,642
Don't do anything stupid.

704
00:53:05,712 --> 00:53:08,042
What's your problem? I
said I'm just going for the files.

705
00:53:08,582 --> 00:53:10,812
And make sure the boss lady is happy.

706
00:53:10,912 --> 00:53:14,182
Knock them dead up
there, all right? Goodness.

707
00:53:28,232 --> 00:53:29,952
(Congratulations on your 10th anniversary.)

708
00:53:40,512 --> 00:53:44,782
- Mom?
- CEO Baek, come say hello.

709
00:53:45,182 --> 00:53:46,382
This is my daughter.

710
00:53:47,682 --> 00:53:51,422
You know who he is, right?
The man making waves in IT.

711
00:53:52,052 --> 00:53:53,622
CEO Baek Tae Ju of The Prime.

712
00:53:54,662 --> 00:53:57,562
- It's a pleasure. I'm Baek Tae Ju.
- I'm Kang Shin Jae.

713
00:53:58,492 --> 00:54:02,262
Why don't you introduce
him around? Mingle a little.

714
00:54:04,832 --> 00:54:06,032
So you're single?

715
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:09,742
Your mother said the same about you.

716
00:54:14,782 --> 00:54:16,622
As it happens, here's
someone you should meet.

717
00:54:18,012 --> 00:54:20,382
- Thanks for coming.
- Of course.

718
00:54:20,452 --> 00:54:21,728
Let me introduce you.

719
00:54:21,752 --> 00:54:23,232
This is CEO Baek Tae Ju of The Prime.

720
00:54:23,552 --> 00:54:25,352
And this is my ex-husband.

721
00:54:26,292 --> 00:54:27,492
I'm Han Seung Hun.

722
00:54:29,062 --> 00:54:30,292
Baek Tae Ju. A pleasure.

723
00:54:30,692 --> 00:54:31,932
I trust you've been well?

724
00:54:33,232 --> 00:54:34,552
I'll be right there. Go on ahead.

725
00:54:38,572 --> 00:54:40,202
And then there's...

726
00:54:41,802 --> 00:54:43,002
Look. There he is.

727
00:54:43,742 --> 00:54:47,112
Over there is my ex-ex-husband.
The second son of the Hanje Group.

728
00:54:50,382 --> 00:54:51,582
Should I bring him over?

729
00:54:52,012 --> 00:54:53,972
I take it your ex-ex-ex-husband
couldn't make it?

730
00:54:55,782 --> 00:54:57,952
Well, I've only managed
to get divorced twice so far.

731
00:54:59,322 --> 00:55:02,662
Though I think my mother
is hoping I'll go for a hat trick.

732
00:55:03,092 --> 00:55:04,292
Mr. Baek,

733
00:55:04,632 --> 00:55:07,532
I'd like you to meet someone.
Shall we head over there?

734
00:55:07,702 --> 00:55:10,332
Of course. And congratulations
on your tenth anniversary.

735
00:55:10,572 --> 00:55:11,772
I'll see you around, then.

736
00:55:12,632 --> 00:55:13,842
Right this way.

737
00:55:18,142 --> 00:55:21,742
I never imagined this would become
a reunion for your ex-husbands.

738
00:55:23,042 --> 00:55:24,962
How could I not invite
them on a day like today?

739
00:55:25,452 --> 00:55:27,652
They're the greatest
contributors in LnJ's history.

740
00:55:28,582 --> 00:55:31,952
If it weren't for my first marriage,
LnJ would never have existed.

741
00:55:32,422 --> 00:55:33,822
And if it weren't for my second,

742
00:55:34,392 --> 00:55:36,592
you would've cut me off
financially ages ago, you know.

743
00:55:38,632 --> 00:55:40,032
I'm not going for a third one, Mom.

744
00:55:40,462 --> 00:55:41,832
So don't waste your breath.

745
00:56:25,872 --> 00:56:27,942
Jun Hyeok, I'm here.

746
00:56:30,652 --> 00:56:31,852
I'm coming in.

747
00:56:32,982 --> 00:56:34,182
Darn it.

748
00:56:48,332 --> 00:56:49,532
Lee Jun Hyeok.

749
00:57:02,642 --> 00:57:06,982
First, I'd like to thank you
all for the last ten years.

750
00:57:07,252 --> 00:57:09,222
Without the help of all of you here today,

751
00:57:09,582 --> 00:57:13,192
we never would have
survived these ten years.

752
00:57:14,062 --> 00:57:17,832
Most of all, I'd like to thank
someone for their constant support.

753
00:57:18,232 --> 00:57:21,332
CEO Seong Tae Im of Haeil,
let's give her a round of applause.

754
00:57:24,932 --> 00:57:26,132
Thank you.

755
00:57:59,932 --> 00:58:01,812
If we couldn't land a
kick, we'd throw a punch.

756
00:58:02,342 --> 00:58:03,982
If a hook didn't connect, we'd use a jab.

757
00:58:04,042 --> 00:58:06,542
And when even a jab wouldn't
work, what choice did we have?

758
00:58:07,412 --> 00:58:09,982
We spent the last ten
years fighting tooth and nail.

759
00:58:10,812 --> 00:58:15,422
But now, after ten years of that,
we can land a hook, and even a kick.

760
00:58:15,852 --> 00:58:17,452
That's the kind of world we live in now.

761
00:58:17,992 --> 00:58:21,562
If we've played even a small part
in making the world a better place,

762
00:58:22,122 --> 00:58:25,062
then for the next decade,
and the one after that,

763
00:58:25,692 --> 00:58:28,002
we will gladly continue the fight.

764
00:58:28,762 --> 00:58:30,572
On the side of the weak and the just.

765
00:58:52,252 --> 00:58:54,292
Shall we all raise a glass?

766
00:59:03,732 --> 00:59:07,172
- To LnJ!
- To LnJ!

767
00:59:49,042 --> 00:59:53,052
(Honour)

768
01:00:30,022 --> 01:00:33,022
I killed someone.

769
01:00:33,592 --> 01:00:34,792
Jun Hyeok.

770
01:00:35,322 --> 01:00:36,562
Lee Jun Hyeok!

771
01:00:36,862 --> 01:00:39,692
Are you saying you're a
suspect in a sexual assault case?

772
01:00:40,432 --> 01:00:42,208
You brought evidence here?
Are you out of your mind?

773
01:00:42,232 --> 01:00:45,472
That ship has sailed. Now
figure out how to stay afloat.

774
01:00:45,702 --> 01:00:47,642
It was stuck in the
mattress. We only found one.

775
01:00:47,702 --> 01:00:51,072
- It was me! I killed him!
- Jo Yoo Jeong.

776
01:00:52,072 --> 01:00:54,142
- Stay away!
- Why you're doing this

777
01:00:54,412 --> 01:00:55,812
I will find out no matter what.
